<div class="extLoad" id="liberiaGov">
  <div class="imgWrapper"><img src="http://akvo.org/wp-content/themes/Akvo-responsive/images/partners/washLiberia.png" title="Government of Liberia" Alt="Government of Liberia" /></div>
  <h1>Government of Liberia</h1>
  <p class="staffTitle">Mapping and monitoring the country's water supply</p>
  <p class="staffBio">
  <p>Built on the lead of its president, Ellen Johnson Sirleaf, Liberia has played a lead role in recent years to realise the water and sanitation elements of the Millennium Development goals. In 2010, an initial version of FLOW was used to map the status of 10,000 water points in the country in partnership with WSP (World Bank) and UNICEF. In 2012, Akvo signed a cooperation agreement to develop the WASH Liberia portal for the government. Akvo RSR will be used to bring the water project portfolio in Liberia online and is assisting in the establishment of a water monitoring unit in the government. The new version of Akvo FLOW will be used to conduct a follow-on mapping exercise with the goal of introducing continuous monitoring. This programme is supported by UNICEF.</p>
  <p class="staffBio"> <a href="http://wash-liberia.org/">wash-liberia.org</a> </p>
</div>
<div class="extLoad" id="partnerWater">
